thread.title: Grain higher, livestock higher

title: Grain higher, livestock higher
text:
Wed, Aug 5, 2015, 1:19 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 8 hrs 41 mins Grain higher, livestock higher Grain higher on the CBOT, beef and pork higher on the CME Associated Press – 31 minutes ago Recommend Print 
CHICAGO (AP) -- Grain futures were higher in early trading Tuesday on the Chicago Board of Trade. 
Wheat for September delivery rose 3 cents to $5.02 a bushel; December corn was 2.25 cents higher at $3.7875 a bushel; December oats were 2.75 cents higher at $2.48 bushel; while November soybeans gained 7.5 cents to 9.43 cents a bushel. 
Beef and pork were higher on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. 
October live cattle was .60 cent higher at $1.4870 a pound; August feeder cattle was .97 cent higher at $2.1482 a pound; October lean hogs rose 1.175 cents to $.6650 a pound. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook RBA happier with dollar and the economy AAP
